lead_paragraph: The 2001 class of free agents is relatively thin, and even some of the star players available are shrouded with question marks. By BUSTER OLNEY Jason Giambi The most dynamic offensive player available and bears a reputation as a tremendous clubhouse leader; big-bodied and 30 years old, he's destined to become a designated hitter if he stays in the American League. Predicted destination: Yankees
